@Giantsfanlewis  I didn't finish Prometheus, I didn't watch Prey. I just looked up his film and tv history, and the only things I saw him in was Without a Trace and The Good Wife, as I was into those shows at that time. I don't remember him in those and had to look up his acting history. I didn't watch Game of Thrones (it should be right up my alley but I was never interested and didn't read the books), and I've not seen any movies he's been in. 

I haven't been to the cinema in over a decade, it was for the second to last Res. Evil movie. A few years ago I dropped cable and all but 1 streaming channel that my husband wants. I watch YouTube and dvds. Lol one thing Hollywood has done is free up more of my budget for hobbies, rather than wasting it on content. Can't even call it entertainment anymore. I watched part of TFA, got super-pissed and never went back to SW. 

Seeing how movies and tv are done these days, I'm amazed so many people still hold out hope for their franchises.

@Cookieboy70 I'll agree with Keanu Reeves being a true star. He didn't have that superstar impact for me 'til Speed. I loved him in Speed and Point Break and I liked him in Parenthood, but he was often cast as a goofball in the early days and it didn't really do it for me. I'm one of the few that never liked Bill and Ted's Excellent Adventure. I loved the premise but just don't like it at all. 

Montalban was a star before I first saw him in the 70s, but that's when I first saw him. Ford had an immediate impact as well as Solo...I saw Star Wars before American Graffiti but people rave about his performance there. Those were the first two I recalled.

Cruise was alright early in his career, Top Gun elevated him to superstar for me.
